achievements.description: Attended a webinar titled Own Your Room and Speak Up, which focused on building confidence, effective communication, and presentation skills. The session provided practical strategies to enhance public speaking and self-expression, helping me gain valuable insight into assertiveness and leadership in both academic and professional settings.

achievements.description: Participated in the webinar Stage to Screen: Master Your Presentation, which explored techniques for delivering impactful presentations both in-person and virtually. The session emphasized body language, voice modulation, and audience engagement strategies. achievements.title: Pregnant Women Examination
achievements.description:
Pregnant Women Examination (Clinical Visit):
Observed and learned the clinical approach to antenatal examination, including history taking and physical assessment of pregnant women. Gained understanding of key signs in maternal health and fetal well-being. This experience improved my confidence in patient interaction and bedside clinical learning.

achievements.title: abdomen examination
achievements.description: Practiced abdominal examination under supervision, focusing on inspection, palpation, percussion, and auscultation. Learned to identify clinical signs related to abdominal pathology and improved examination techniques. This strengthened my foundation in systematic patient assessment.

achievements.title: barirer to participation in preventive health checkup , cross sectional study
achievements.description: Conducted a cross-sectional study on barriers to participation in preventive health checkups. Explored factors influencing patient awareness, accessibility, and attitudes towards preventive care. The study provided valuable insights into improving health-seeking behavior and strengthening community health initiatives.

achievements.title: validity study of WHOQOL-BREF assessment in general surgery patients in rawalpindi
achievements.description: Carried out a validity study of the WHOQOL-BREF questionnaire among general surgery patients in Rawalpindi. Assessed its reliability and applicability in measuring quality of life within this patient population. The study highlighted its potential as a valuable tool for patient-centered care and surgical outcome evaluation.

achievements.title: poster on fatty liver disease
achievements.description: Designed an educational poster on fatty liver disease, highlighting its causes, risk factors, and preventive measures. The poster aimed to raise awareness among patients and peers about lifestyle modifications for better liver health. This activity enhanced my skills in medical communication and visual learning.

achievements.title: webinar on Career Scope in Neurosurgery,
achievements.description: Attended a webinar on Career Scope in Neurosurgery, which provided insights into training pathways, subspecialties, and challenges in the field. The session offered valuable guidance on academic preparation, research involvement, and skill development required for pursuing neurosurgery. It broadened my understanding of surgical career planning and inspired me to work towards my long-term goals.

achievements.title: rewire ur brain to smoking weboinar
achievements.description:
I attended a webinar on Rewire Your Brain to Quit Smoking which focused on the neurobiological basis of addiction.
The session emphasized psychological strategies and behavioral modifications to overcome smoking habits.
It deepened my understanding of how mindset shifts play a vital role in breaking addictive cycles.

reflections.title: tb awareness campaign
reflections.content: I participated in organizing a Tuberculosis Awareness Campaign aimed at educating patients and community members about TB prevention, early detection, and treatment. The campaign included interactive discussions, distribution of informational material, and direct engagement with the audience to address misconceptions. Through this activity, I developed skills in public health communication, teamwork, and community outreach while contributing to raising awareness about a major health issue.

reflections.title: conducted spelling bee segment at MIG olymoiad
reflections.content: I conducted the Spelling Bee segment at the MIG Olympiad, where I was responsible for organizing, coordinating, and ensuring the smooth flow of the competition. This role required planning, time management, and active engagement with participants. The experience strengthened my leadership, organizational, and communication skills while giving me confidence in managing academic events.

reflections.title: Health Information Desk
reflections.content:
I participated in a Health Information Desk activity where we guided people about common health issues.
We provided awareness on preventive measures, lifestyle changes, and importance of regular check-ups.
This experience improved my communication skills and confidence in community interaction.

reflections.title: briefing before ece
reflections.content:
The briefing sessions before ECE provided a clear overview of the days objectives and flow.
They helped me understand the clinical relevance of topics and stay more engaged during learning.
This practice enhanced my preparedness and gave valuable insights into clinical exposure.
